owl:Ontology.rdfs:label: ft3
owl:Ontology.dcmi-terms:creator: Mar√≠a Navas-Loro
owl:Ontology.dcmi-terms:description: Ontology to support temporal information annotation
owl:Ontology.dcmi-terms:title: Ontology to support temporal information annotation.
fromTimeToTime

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An alternative way to represent the information provided by an Annotation; for instance, a sem:Time would be an alternative value for a TIMEX3 annotation.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: alternativeValue

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: AND relation to combine [TemporalExpressions](http://fromtimetotime.linkeddata.es/ontology/fromtimetotime#TemporalExpression). in a [ComposedTemporalExpression](http://fromtimetotime.linkeddata.es/ontology/fromtimetotime#ComposedTemporalExpression).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: and

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The information represented by an annotation.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: annotationOf

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Connects an Annotation with the AnnotationSchema it implements.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: followsSchema

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: NOT relation to negate a [TemporalExpression](http://fromtimetotime.linkeddata.es/ontology/fromtimetotime#TemporalExpression) in a [ComposedTemporalExpression](http://fromtimetotime.linkeddata.es/ontology/fromtimetotime#ComposedTemporalExpression).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: not

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: OR relation to combine [TemporalExpressions](http://fromtimetotime.linkeddata.es/ontology/fromtimetotime#TemporalExpression) in a [ComposedTemporalExpression](http://fromtimetotime.linkeddata.es/ontology/fromtimetotime#ComposedTemporalExpression).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: or

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Allows to represent and associate an annotation format to the different annotations in a document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: AnnotationSchema

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Abstract class to represent the arguments of the different annotation standards.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Argument

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class allows to create a composed temporal expression, combining different temporal expressions with the operators OR, AND or NOT.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ComposedTemporalExpression

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class to represent an annotated document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Document

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Annotation of the type EVENT from the TimeML standard
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EVENTannotation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Abstract class of the arguments of the EVENT annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EVENTargument

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument CLASS of a EVENT annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EVENTclass

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument EID of a EVENT annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EVENTeid

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument STEM of a EVENT annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EVENTstem

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A formal representation of an event, such as a frame from Framenet, VerbNet or another semantic repository.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EventFormalization

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An instance of an event. In the example "he went jogging on Tuesday and Wednesday", there would be one mention but two instances: one on Tuesday and another one on Wednesday.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EventInstance

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The textual mention of an event.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EventMention

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The schematic representation of an event.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EventSchematization

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Annotation from the EventsMatter corpus format. It allows to represent events through annotations of different types (when, what, who, event) sharing an id.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EventsMatterAnnotation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Annotation from the EventsMatter corpus format. It allows to represent the context of an event.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EventsMatterEvent

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Annotation from the EventsMatter corpus format. It allows to represent the core of an event, meaning what happened.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EventsMatterEvent_what

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Annotation from the EventsMatter corpus format. It allows to represent the when an event happened.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EventsMatterEvent_when

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Annotation from the EventsMatter corpus format. It allows to represent the who carried out the event.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EventsMatterEvent_who

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Identifier of an annotation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ID

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Annotation of the type MAKEINSTANCE from the TimeML standard. It represents instances of events.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: MAKEINSTANCEannotation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Abstract class of the arguments of the MAKEINSTANCE annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: MAKEINSTANCEargument

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument ASPECT of a MAKEINSTANCE annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: MAKEINSTANCEaspect

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument CARDINALITY of a MAKEINSTANCE annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: MAKEINSTANCEcardinality

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument EIID of a MAKEINSTANCE annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: MAKEINSTANCEeiid

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument MODALITY of a MAKEINSTANCE annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: MAKEINSTANCEmodality

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument POLARITY of a MAKEINSTANCE annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: MAKEINSTANCEpolarity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument POS of a MAKEINSTANCE annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: MAKEINSTANCEpos

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument TENSE of a MAKEINSTANCE annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: MAKEINSTANCEtense

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents a temporal expression that repeats over time (e.g. Once a week). In the TimeML standard it would correspond to a SET temporal expression.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RepetitiveTime

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Any possible restriction to a sem:Time class.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Restriction

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Annotation of the type SIGNAL from the TimeML standard. It allows to mark up words with a temporal meaning that are not relations, temporal expressions or events.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SIGNALannotation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Abstract class of the arguments of the SIGNAL annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SIGNALargument

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument SID of a SIGNAL annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SIGNALsid

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument TIMEX3TemporalFunctionID of a TIMEX3 annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TIMEX3TemporalFunctionID

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Annotation of the type TIMEX3 from the TimeML standard. It allows to represent temporal expressions (dates, times...)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TIMEX3annotation
TIMEX3argument
owl:Class.dcmi-terms:description: Abstract class of the arguments of the TIMEX3 annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument TIMEX3beginPoint of a TIMEX3 annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TIMEX3beginPoint

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument TIMEX3endPoint of a TIMEX3 annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TIMEX3endPoint

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument FREQ of a TIMEX3 annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TIMEX3freq

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument functionInDocument of a TIMEX3 annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TIMEX3functionInDocument

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument MOD of a TIMEX3 annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TIMEX3mod

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument QUANT of a TIMEX3 annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TIMEX3quant

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument temporalFunction of a TIMEX3 annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TIMEX3temporalFunction

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument TID of a TIMEX3 annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TIMEX3tid

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument TYPE of a TIMEX3 annotation from the TimeML annotation standard. It can be ft3:DATE, ft3:SET, ft3:DURATION or ft3:TIME.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TIMEX3type

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument VALUE of a TIMEX3 annotation from the TimeML annotation standard. It can take different formats depending on the TYPE of annotation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TIMEX3value

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Argument valueFromFunction of a TIMEX3 annotation from the TimeML annotation standard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TIMEX3valueFromFunction

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class represents a temporal expression, meaning a expression representing any temporal reference.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TemporalExpression

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A possible restriction to a sem:Time expression is a temporal relation, such as "before"
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TemporalRelation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents the repetition times of a repetitive expression, with an amount (value) and timeunit.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Times

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents the type of an annotation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Type

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class Instance from GAF, representing an instance of an annotation in text.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Instance

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class Mention from GAF, representing a mention of an annotation in text.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Mention

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represenents an annotation of any kind, usually NLP.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Annotation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represenents an annotation of any kind, usually NLP.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: annotationUnit

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents an entity involved in an Event, usually who carried out the action.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Actor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents an event, in the broadest sense of the term.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Event

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class represents the information of any temporal expression.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Time

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents a time/date temporal expression (e.g. Tomorrow at eight o'clock). In the TimeML standard it would correspond to a DATE or a TIME temporal expression.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: GeneralDateTimeDescription

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents a duration temporal expression (e.g. Two days). In the TimeML standard it would correspond to a DURATION temporal expression.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: GeneralDurationDescription

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Interval representation from the TimeOntology.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Interval

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Describes the granularity of the repretition in a repetitive temporal expression.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TimeUnit

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Periodic Time Interval is a possible way to represent a periodic event in the TEO ontology.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PeriodicTimeInterval

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents an interval from the TEO ontology.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TemporalInterval
